# UI/UX Design Best Practices

Reference: [cursor.directory/ui-ux-design-best-practices](https://cursor.directory/ui-ux-design-best-practices)

## Visual Design

### Visual Hierarchy
- Establish clear visual hierarchy to guide user attention
- Use size, color, contrast, and spacing to indicate importance
- Primary actions should be visually prominent
- Group related elements together

### Color Palette
- Use the existing CSS variables in `globals.css` for theming
- Maintain brand consistency across the application
- Use semantic colors: `destructive` for errors, `primary` for actions
- Ensure color is not the only indicator of meaning (accessibility)

```tsx
// Good: Using theme colors
<Button variant="destructive">Delete</Button>
<span className="text-muted-foreground">Secondary text</span>

// Bad: Hardcoded colors
<button className="bg-red-500">Delete</button>
```

### Typography
- Use the font scale defined in Tailwind config
- Limit to 2-3 font sizes per component
- Use `font-medium` or `font-semibold` for emphasis, not bold everywhere
- Ensure readable line lengths (45-75 characters for body text)

```tsx
// Typography scale
<h1 className="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight">Page Title</h1>
<h2 className="text-2xl font-semibold">Section Title</h2>
<p className="text-base text-muted-foreground">Body text</p>
<span className="text-sm">Small text</span>
```

### Contrast & Accessibility
- Maintain WCAG 2.1 AA contrast ratios (4.5:1 for text, 3:1 for large text)
- Test with both light and dark themes
- Use `text-foreground` and `text-muted-foreground` for proper contrast

## Interaction Design

### Navigation
- Keep navigation consistent across pages
- Use breadcrumbs for deep hierarchies
- Highlight current location in nav
- Provide clear "back" options

### UI Components
- Use familiar patterns (don't reinvent standard components)
- Keep interactive elements recognizable (buttons look clickable)
- Use shadcn/ui components for consistency
- Minimum touch target size: 44x44px for mobile

### Calls-to-Action (CTAs)
- One primary CTA per view/section
- Use action verbs: "Create Account" not "Submit"
- Make CTAs visually distinct from other elements

```tsx
// Good: Clear primary action
<div className="flex gap-2">
  <Button variant="outline">Cancel</Button>
  <Button>Save Changes</Button>
</div>

// Bad: Competing primary actions
<div className="flex gap-2">
  <Button>Cancel</Button>
  <Button>Save</Button>
</div>
```

### Responsive Design
- Mobile-first approach: design for small screens, then scale up
- Use Tailwind responsive prefixes: `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`
- Test at common breakpoints: 375px, 768px, 1024px, 1280px

```tsx
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
  {/* Cards that stack on mobile, 2-col on tablet, 3-col on desktop */}
</div>
```

### Animations & Transitions
- Use animations purposefully (guide attention, provide feedback)
- Keep animations short: 150-300ms for micro-interactions
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`

```tsx
// Motion-safe animations
<div className="transition-all duration-200 hover:scale-105 motion-reduce:transform-none">
  Content
</div>
```

## Accessibility

### Semantic HTML
```tsx
// Good: Semantic structure
<main>
  <header>
    <nav aria-label="Main navigation">...</nav>
  </header>
  <article>
    <h1>Title</h1>
    <section aria-labelledby="section-title">
      <h2 id="section-title">Section</h2>
    </section>
  </article>
</main>

// Bad: Div soup
<div>
  <div>
    <div>...</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Keyboard Navigation
- All interactive elements must be keyboard accessible
- Visible focus indicators (don't remove `outline`)
- Logical tab order (follows visual order)
- Use `focus-visible` for mouse/keyboard differentiation

```tsx
<button className="focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2">
  Click me
</button>
```

### Screen Readers
- Provide `alt` text for meaningful images
- Use `aria-label` for icon-only buttons
- Hide decorative elements: `aria-hidden="true"`
- Announce dynamic content changes

```tsx
// Icon button with label
<Button size="icon" aria-label="Close dialog">
  <X className="h-4 w-4" />
</Button>

// Decorative image
<img src="/decoration.svg" alt="" aria-hidden="true" />
```

## User Feedback

### Loading States
- Show loading indicators for async operations
- Use skeleton loaders for content areas
- Disable buttons during submission

```tsx
<Button disabled={isLoading}>
  {isLoading && <Loader2 className="mr-2 h-4 w-4 animate-spin" />}
  {isLoading ? "Saving..." : "Save Changes"}
</Button>
```

### Error Handling
- Show errors near the source (inline validation)
- Provide clear recovery actions
- Use `destructive` variant for error states
- Don't just show "Error" - explain what went wrong

```tsx
// Form field with error
<div className="space-y-2">
  <Label htmlFor="email">Email</Label>
  <Input
    id="email"
    aria-invalid={!!error}
    aria-describedby={error ? "email-error" : undefined}
    className={error ? "border-destructive" : ""}
  />
  {error && (
    <p id="email-error" className="text-sm text-destructive">
      {error}
    </p>
  )}
</div>
```

### Success Feedback
- Confirm successful actions clearly
- Use toast notifications for non-blocking feedback
- Provide next steps when appropriate

```tsx
import { toast } from "sonner";

// Success feedback
toast.success("Changes saved successfully");

// With action
toast.success("Profile updated", {
  action: {
    label: "View Profile",
    onClick: () => router.push("/profile"),
  },
});
```

## Mobile-First Design

### Touch-Friendly Elements
- Minimum touch target: 44x44px
- Adequate spacing between touch targets (8px minimum)
- Consider thumb zones for important actions

```tsx
// Touch-friendly list items
<button className="flex items-center gap-3 w-full p-4 min-h-[44px]">
  <Icon className="h-5 w-5" />
  <span>Menu Item</span>
</button>
```

### Mobile Navigation Patterns
- Use bottom navigation for primary actions on mobile
- Hamburger menu for secondary navigation
- Consider swipe gestures for common actions

### Responsive Images
```tsx
import Image from "next/image";

<Image
  src="/hero.jpg"
  alt="Hero image"
  width={1200}
  height={600}
  sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, (max-width: 1200px) 50vw, 33vw"
  className="object-cover"
  priority // for above-the-fold images
/>
```

## Information Architecture

### Content Organization
- Group related items together
- Use progressive disclosure (show more on demand)
- Limit choices to avoid decision paralysis (7±2 rule)

### Clear Labeling
- Use descriptive, user-friendly labels
- Avoid jargon and technical terms
- Be consistent with terminology

### Search & Filtering
- Provide search for large data sets
- Show active filters clearly
- Allow easy filter clearing

## Consistency

### Design System Usage
- Use shadcn/ui components consistently
- Don't create custom components when existing ones work
- Follow established patterns for common UI elements

### Spacing System
Use Tailwind's spacing scale consistently:
- `gap-2` (8px) - tight grouping
- `gap-4` (16px) - related elements
- `gap-6` (24px) - section spacing
- `gap-8` (32px) - major sections

```tsx
// Consistent card layout
<Card className="p-6">
  <CardHeader className="space-y-2">
    <CardTitle>Title</CardTitle>
    <CardDescription>Description</CardDescription>
  </CardHeader>
  <CardContent className="space-y-4">
    {/* Content with consistent spacing */}
  </CardContent>
  <CardFooter className="gap-2">
    <Button variant="outline">Cancel</Button>
    <Button>Confirm</Button>
  </CardFooter>
</Card>
```

## Prototyping Checklist

When building new UI:

```
□ Visual Hierarchy - Is the most important element obvious?
□ Mobile First - Does it work on a 375px screen?
□ Touch Targets - Are buttons/links at least 44px?
□ Loading States - What shows during async operations?
□ Error States - How are errors displayed?
□ Empty States - What shows when there's no data?
□ Keyboard Navigation - Can you tab through everything?
□ Dark Mode - Does it look good in both themes?
□ Contrast - Is text readable against backgrounds?
□ Feedback - Does the user know their action worked?
```

